OL,3,CAndy Burnham becomes UK's 7th prime
OL,4,Cminister in a decade - how did we get
OL,5,Chere?
OL,7,FLiz Truss (September 2022 - October
OL,8,F2022)
OL,10,FLiz Truss holds the record for the
OL,11,Fshortest stint as prime minister in
OL,12,FBritish history, at just 49 days.
OL,14,FAfter winning the Conservative
OL,15,Fleadership election, Truss was faced
OL,16,Fwith a challenging in-tray as the cost
OL,17,Fof living soared in the wake of
OL,18,FRussia's full-scale invasion of
OL,19,FUkraine in February 2022.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31614
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1784569706
OL,3,CAndy Burnham becomes UK's 7th prime
OL,4,Cminister in a decade - how did we get
OL,5,Chere?
OL,7,FShe promised a "bold plan" to cut
OL,8,Ftaxes and grow the economy, but her
OL,9,Fmini-budget rocked financial markets,
OL,10,Fsent the pound plummeting and prompted
OL,11,Fa revolt within her own party.
OL,13,FTruss became the last prime minister
OL,14,Fto meet the late Queen, who died two
OL,15,Fdays after meeting her at Balmoral.
OL,16,FQueen Elizabeth II's death triggered a
OL,17,Ften-day national mourning period.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31615
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1784569706
OL,3,CAndy Burnham becomes UK's 7th prime
OL,4,Cminister in a decade - how did we get
OL,5,Chere?
OL,7,FPerhaps one of the most famous moments
OL,8,Fof her short time in office was the
OL,9,FDaily Star newspaper's livestream of a
OL,10,Flettuce to see whether the vegetable
OL,11,Fcould last longer than the PM. The
OL,12,Flettuce became a viral sensation and
OL,13,Fdid, in fact, outlast Truss.
OL,15,FRishi Sunak (October 2022 - July 2024)
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31616
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1784569706
OL,3,CAndy Burnham becomes UK's 7th prime
OL,4,Cminister in a decade - how did we get
OL,5,Chere?
OL,7,FWhen he took over from Truss, Rishi
OL,8,FSunak became the country's first
OL,9,Fperson from an ethnic minority and a
OL,10,FHindu background to lead the country,
OL,11,Fas well as being the youngest to do so
OL,12,Ffor more than 200 years.
OL,14,FHis biggest job was to stabilise the
OL,15,Feconomy after Truss' tenure, but he
OL,16,Falso oversaw the government's
OL,17,Fimplementation of the Rwanda asylum
OL,18,Fplan and scrapped the HS2 leg to
OL,19,FManchester before he called a snap
OL,20,FGeneral Election in May 2024.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31617
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1784569706
OL,3,CAndy Burnham becomes UK's 7th prime
OL,4,Cminister in a decade - how did we get
OL,5,Chere?
OL,7,FOther notable moments from Sunak's
OL,8,Ftime at No 10 include the widespread
OL,9,Fbacklash he received for opting to
OL,10,Fleave a D-Day commemoration event
OL,11,Fearly to do an ITV News interview, in
OL,12,Fwhich he famously said he "couldn't
OL,13,Fhave Sky TV" as a child.
OL,15,FHis resignation speech featured an
OL,16,Felement of pathetic fallacy as he was
OL,17,Fdoused in rain outside Downing Street.
OL,19,FKeir Starmer (July 2024 - July 2026)
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31618
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1784569706
OL,3,CAndy Burnham becomes UK's 7th prime
OL,4,Cminister in a decade - how did we get
OL,5,Chere?
OL,7,FSunak calling an election led to a
OL,8,Flandslide Labour majority, led by Sir
OL,9,FKeir Starmer, that ended 14 years of
OL,10,FConservative leadership.
OL,12,FLabour won 411 seats, up 209 on their
OL,13,Ftotal from the 2019 election and the
OL,14,Fbiggest gain in seats since 1945.
OL,16,FStarmer pledged to kickstart the
OL,17,Feconomy, make Britain a "clean energy
OL,18,Fsuperpower" and rejuvenate the NHS,
OL,19,Fbut setbacks and scandals overshadowed
OL,20,Fparts of his premiership.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31619
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1784569706
OL,3,CAndy Burnham becomes UK's 7th prime
OL,4,Cminister in a decade - how did we get
OL,5,Chere?
OL,7,FU-turns on the winter fuel allowance,
OL,8,Fthe two-child benefit cap and
OL,9,Fmandatory digital IDs dominated the
OL,10,Fheadlines, until Peter Mandelson's
OL,11,Ffriendship with convicted paedophile
OL,12,FJeffrey Epstein came to light.
OL,14,FStarmer came under continued pressure
OL,15,Fover his decision to appoint Mandelson
OL,16,Fas US ambassador, and that, paired
OL,17,Fwith poor local election results, led
OL,18,Fto his downfall.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/21
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
